  "text": "Clearly, if a system has a noise level which is equal or greater than ∆I the zero order fringe peak cannot be identified directly, simply through inspection of its amplitude. If the normalized zero order fringe peak value is defined as unit signal, a minimum signal-to-noise ratio SNR min required to identify the zero order fringe peak [CITATION_1] is given by",
